    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University Hospital, Angers</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to evaluate the impact of nasal continuous positive airway pressure (nCPAP)
      treatment on liver enzymes in patients with sleep apnea syndrome and nonalcoholic
      steatohepatitis. Using a cross over design, the evolution of liver enzymes will be evaluated
      in 40 patients during a consecutive period of 6 weeks, with and without nCPAP treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
